title: SUBMISSION OF CONCURRENT AND SENATE RESOLUTIONS

content.text:
The following concurrent resolutions and Senate resolutions were 
read, and referred (or acted upon), as indicated:
content.speaker: Unknown

content.text:
By Mr. MANCHIN (for himself and Mrs. Capito):
       S. Res. 332. A resolution commemorating the christening of 
     the USNS Hershel ``Woody'' Williams; considered and agreed 
     to.
content.speaker: The RECORDER

content.text:
By Mr. ISAKSON (for himself and Mr. Tester):
       S. Res. 333. A resolution permitting the collection of 
     clothing, toys, food, and housewares during the holiday 
     season for charitable purposes in Senate buildings; 
     considered and agreed to.
content.speaker: The RECORDER

content.text:
By Mr. McCONNELL (for himself and Mr. Schumer):
       S. Res. 334. A resolution authorizing the taking of a 
     photograph in the Senate Chamber; considered and agreed to.
content.speaker: The RECORDER
